node.title: NT records three new cases of COVID linked to Katherine cluster
node.alt: Two men talking under a marquee outside a COVID-19 testing centre.
node.description: Three more local COVID-19 cases are recorded in the NT overnight, bringing the total number of cases linked to the Katherine cluster to 56.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded three local COVID-19 cases in 24 hours related to the Katherine cluster.\u00a0\u00a0", "The three new cases are a man in his 40s from Katherine, a woman in her 20s from Robinson River and a male child under 10 from Robinson River.", "It brings the total number of cases linked to the\u00a0local cluster to 56.", "Chief Minister Michael Gunner said all three cases are\u00a0household contacts and have\u00a0been in the Howard Springs quarantine facility for the whole of their infectious periods.\u00a0", "Mr Gunner said the trio had tested positive late in their 14-day quarantine periods, which meant they may have caught the virus while in Howard Springs\u00a0as a result of \"family mingling\".", "He said the rules around mingling in Howard Springs had since been tightened.", "Some people staying in the facility will have their quarantine periods lengthened as a result.", "A fourth case recorded in the NT overnight was a flight crew member who arrived from London on a repatriation flight.", "More to come."]
